":"autoMapInputData","value":{},"matchingColumns":[],"schema":[]},"options":{}},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.googleSheets","typeVersion":4.7,"position":[10098,1420],"id":"2480bc50-0e28-45e8-9256-81e31bfa6349","name":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","retryOnFail":true,"maxTries":3,"waitBetweenTries":2000},{"parameters":{"content":"### Receive Inbound Webhook\n\nEntry point: listens for POST calls on `/wf09235-order`. Use the TEST url while building, switch callers to the PRODUCTION url after publishing.\n\nNext: Compute HMAC Signature","width":280,"height":232,"color":5},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-330,520],"id":"b1cb2dd4-bd0c-5c3b-1cae-39a0a48bf8dc","name":"Note: Receive Inbound Webhook"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute HMAC Signature\n\nComputes the HMAC-SHA256 of the raw payload to verify the sender's signature before trusting the data.\n\nNext: Signature Valid?","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-6,520],"id":"dae1c081-cbe0-a169-5139-f13177f5ee75","name":"Note: Compute HMAC Signature"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Signature Valid?\n\nTwo-way gate on `={{ $json.computedSignature === $json.headers['x-signature']`. TRUE continues the happy path, FALSE takes the alternate branch.\n\nPorts: ①→ Map to Canonical Schema · ②→ Reject (HTTP 401)","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[318,520],"id":"eaea2bc2-a342-3ebd-a26c-333ebec214bb","name":"Note: Signature Valid?"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Reject (HTTP 401)\n\nSends the HTTP 401 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[642,1000],"id":"0ddab581-8b95-8597-3f55-fdcb5ba082f5","name":"Note: Reject (HTTP 401)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Map to Canonical Schema\n\nShapes the item: writes `orderId`, `kind`, `payload`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[966,520],"id":"162ad2a1-a19f-9ca2-4303-a1e7bc32eedf","name":"Note: Map to Canonical Schema"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202)\n\nSends the HTTP 202 response back to the caller — keep this fast; heavy work happens after/async.\n\nNext: Route by Event Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1290,520],"id":"307c92e5-f820-84bc-b8c9-04a50ee93d58","name":"Note: Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Route by Event Kind\n\nRoutes each item to one of 4 lanes: opened, closed, reopened + fallback.\n\nPorts: ①→ Handle 'opened' → Notion · ②→ Handle 'closed' → Forward API · ③→ Handle 'reopened' → Forward API · ④→ Log Unrecognized Kind","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1614,520],"id":"a13d2d48-c031-aeb5-778f-cbdb15b8e990","name":"Note: Route by Event Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'opened' → Notion\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1938,250],"id":"1c3cf5a2-cd3a-b342-930b-48d9ce720283","name":"Note: Handle 'opened' → Notion"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'closed' → Forward API\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/orders — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2262,760],"id":"fac22ca0-8855-d581-6468-4f853e2a28c4","name":"Note: Handle 'closed' → Forward API"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Handle 'reopened' → Forward API\n\nPOST https://api.example.com/v1/orders — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2586,1270],"id":"cffcfdf2-f9f8-47b2-5749-d66a70a48dc9","name":"Note: Handle 'reopened' → Forward API"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Log Unrecognized Kind\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Consolidate Handling · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[2910,1780],"id":"1d6a14bf-a956-596f-56ba-c230d3c1f99a","name":"Note: Log Unrecognized Kind"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Consolidate Handling\n\nRejoins 4 branches into one stream (mode: append) so downstream logic runs once.\n\nNext: Fingerprint for Idempotency","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[3558,520],"id":"df29f3bc-1e6d-6290-52e9-00ce8aafe64f","name":"Note: Consolidate Handling"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fingerprint for Idempotency\n\nCustom JavaScript: Build a stable idempotency key per order (djb2 hash, no deps)\n\nNext: Drop Already-Processed Items","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4530,520],"id":"3c10d762-0b19-6423-09cc-0c5c8ca8870e","name":"Note: Fingerprint for Idempotency"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Drop Already-Processed Items\n\nCross-execution dedupe: remembers keys it has processed before and drops repeats — the idempotency guard.\n\nNext: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[4854,520],"id":"98db85d8-b3f7-a384-db41-363d32f6fe23","name":"Note: Drop Already-Processed Items"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow\n\nDelegates to a reusable sub-workflow (single-responsibility building block) and waits for its result.\n\nPorts: ①→ Record Sub-workflow Result · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5178,520],"id":"e685a8c0-67de-1f77-3945-e8d85b67e926","name":"Note: Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Record Sub-workflow Result\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Serialize Run Output (CSV)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5502,520],"id":"10706c26-49b3-9b7f-3069-134d664da4fb","name":"Note: Record Sub-workflow Result"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Serialize Run Output (CSV)\n\nSerializes items to a CSV binary file.\n\nNext: Archive Row Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[5826,520],"id":"8622871b-b7ab-7e6f-805c-cbf42e627db5","name":"Note: Serialize Run Output (CSV)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Archive Row Snapshot\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Stamp Completion Time · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6150,520],"id":"e524dfae-4b50-552a-3084-8d6aa4d19f30","name":"Note: Archive Row Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Stamp Completion Time\n\nStamps `completedAt` with the current time for auditing.\n\nNext: Persist Run Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6474,520],"id":"85cb2649-a959-2c89-1850-8e08908c8101","name":"Note: Stamp Completion Time"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Persist Run Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Enrich with Reference Data","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[6798,520],"id":"82f57cfc-96d5-147e-129f-414cd5941466","name":"Note: Persist Run Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Enrich with Reference Data\n\nGET https://enrichment.example.com/v2/lookup — retries 3× with backoff on failure.\n\nPorts: ①→ Fold In Enrichment Fields · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 API key / bearer for the target API","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7122,520],"id":"7cbc3965-fca1-656d-b610-2af6ec6d2433","name":"Note: Enrich with Reference Data"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Fold In Enrichment Fields\n\nShapes the item: writes `enrichedAt`, `enrichmentSource`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Load Previous Snapshot","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7446,520],"id":"3434c591-4f5b-9a86-bdfc-646205348ade","name":"Note: Fold In Enrichment Fields"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Load Previous Snapshot\n\nReads every row from 'Order Tracker' — the read side of the store, e.g. for a digest or a downstream sync.\n\nPorts: ①→ Compute Drift vs Snapshot · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[7770,520],"id":"ee6e3765-4ab3-213b-d578-6c55e21de73d","name":"Note: Load Previous Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Compute Drift vs Snapshot\n\nCustom JavaScript: Compare current metrics with the previous snapshot\n\nNext: Guard Non-Empty email","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8094,520],"id":"2a381c98-1b46-f61c-433a-2ed7d65d1e0f","name":"Note: Compute Drift vs Snapshot"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Guard Non-Empty email\n\nDrops items that fail the condition; only qualifying items continue (no false branch).\n\nNext: Save Execution Metadata","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8418,520],"id":"c1c41108-8c2b-75f9-32c5-f534da91c9b6","name":"Note: Guard Non-Empty email"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Save Execution Metadata\n\nSaves key fields onto the execution record — searchable later in n8n's execution list.\n\nNext: Sort Orders Newest First","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[8742,520],"id":"b05967f4-7291-c96b-b02d-befe67e447cb","name":"Note: Save Execution Metadata"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Sort Orders Newest First\n\nOrders items (newest first) so limits and digests pick the most relevant records.\n\nNext: Summarize Run Stats","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9066,520],"id":"88d24731-fd2e-fe0a-5dc2-3da3940a5c38","name":"Note: Sort Orders Newest First"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Summarize Run Stats\n\nShapes the item: writes `runAt`, `itemCount`, `status`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Append Audit Row (Notion)","width":280,"height":232,"color":7},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,520],"id":"b99fb80e-1ee0-52bc-9685-8e7390c35ca2","name":"Note: Summarize Run Stats"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Append Audit Row (Notion)\n\nCreates a new page in the Notion database — the title is pulled straight from the item's key field.\n\nPorts: ①→ Send Summary to Microsoft Teams · ②→ Capture Failure Context\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Notion integration token","width":280,"height":232,"color":2},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,520],"id":"91948226-93df-b0f0-adee-d49b5b064b52","name":"Note: Append Audit Row (Notion)"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Send Summary to Microsoft Teams\n\nPosts a chat message into a Microsoft Teams channel — same role as a Slack notify, for teams standardized on Teams.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · ⚠ failures exit via the error rail · 🔑 Microsoft OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,520],"id":"73ccd02a-496a-35ac-6d29-9e3ab50c5b0f","name":"Note: Send Summary to Microsoft Teams"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Capture Failure Context\n\nShapes the item: writes `failedNode`, `errorMessage`, `workflow`. Keeps the schema explicit between stages.\n\nNext: Escalate Failure to Slack","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9390,1540],"id":"e41332bc-461b-2ec5-dfbd-29dcc5facb2a","name":"Note: Capture Failure Context"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Escalate Failure to Slack\n\nPosts a message to Slack (`#orders`) — a low-latency way for the team to see automation activity without checking a dashboard.\n\nNext: Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Slack OAuth2","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[9714,1540],"id":"543f6d05-47b9-aa3b-6f2c-67c00000467d","name":"Note: Escalate Failure to Slack"},{"parameters":{"content":"### Park in Dead-Letter Queue\n\nAppends a new row to 'Order Tracker' — a human-readable audit trail that doesn't require opening n8n to inspect.\n\n↻ retries 3×/2s · 🔑 Google OAuth2 / service account","width":280,"height":232,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[10038,1540],"id":"580aed14-0fc5-718a-e16f-df02f41782d6","name":"Note: Park in Dead-Letter Queue"},{"parameters":{"content":"# Broadcast the team on new events with Microsoft Teams\n\n**Pattern:** Event Notification · **Level:** Architect · **Trigger:** Webhook\n\n## What it does\nBroadcast the team on new events with Microsoft Teams. It fires the moment an external system calls its webhook.\n\n## Why it exists\nManual order ops is slow and error-prone; this workflow makes the process repeatable, monitored and hands-off, with failures surfaced instead of silently lost.\n\n## Main flow\nReceive Inbound Webhook → Compute HMAC Signature → Signature Valid? → Map to Canonical Schema → Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202) → Route by Event Kind → Handle 'opened' → Notion → …\n\n## Use it for\n- Teams that want to event notification without manual effort\n- Anyone automating order ops in e-commerce\n- Replacing a fragile manual process with a reliable workflow\n\n## You get\n- Scales without extra headcount\n- Saves hours of manual work each week\n- Runs 24/7 in the background\n\n## Before first run\nConnect credentials: API key / bearer for the target API; Google OAuth2 / service account; Microsoft OAuth2; Notion integration token; Slack OAuth2.\nFollow the color key: 🟦 entry · 🟪 AI · 🟫 actions · ⬜ utilities · 🟩 outputs · 🟥 error rail.\nEach node has its own doc card underneath — read those before editing.\n\n## Try it now\nSample data is pinned on the trigger — hit **Execute Workflow** to watch it flow through every node before connecting any real credentials. Unpin the trigger (right-click → Unpin) when you're ready to go live.","width":480,"height":900},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,80],"id":"a84a33e7-4d80-0b3c-f99b-5d9b5a0e48dd","name":"📘 Workflow Overview"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Design decisions\n\nThe optional HMAC check runs before any business logic touches the payload — bad signatures are rejected at the door rather than after work has already been done with untrusted data. Acking fast (HTTP 202) and doing the real work after the response is what stops the sender's webhook delivery from timing out and re-delivering the same event.","width":480,"height":300,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1020],"id":"8e9be2b6-d191-4920-32d5-09d6d4f60c5f","name":"🎓 Design Decisions"},{"parameters":{"content":"## Practice exercises\n\nAbout as deep as this pattern goes — extend it:\n\n1. Turn on signature verification and trace what a tampered payload does at the 'Signature Valid?' gate.\n2. Add a new event kind to the switch and give it its own handler.\n3. Remove the fast-ack step and observe how response time changes under a slow downstream write.","width":480,"height":340,"color":6},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-830,1360],"id":"df1ddb04-9de1-aaa3-7e69-f07aa9afbf15","name":"🧪 Practice Exercises"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛟 Error handling & retries\n\nExternal calls retry **3× with 2s backoff**. Anything still failing exits through its node's error output into the red error rail → context is captured and the on-call channel is alerted. Failures are also parked in a dead-letter queue for replay. Set an n8n **Error Workflow** in settings as the final safety net.","width":360,"height":260,"color":3},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[-230,-290],"id":"e9744480-6f5b-485c-1808-dc6dd6555b28","name":"🛟 Error handling & retries"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🔐 Security\n\nNever trust inbound payloads: the webhook path is unguessable, and the HMAC signature is verified before any processing. Add header auth or IP allow-listing for defense in depth. Secrets live in n8n credentials — never in node parameters.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[190,-290],"id":"380a161b-a61d-ad8e-b9dc-19fd50f937a5","name":"🔐 Security"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🧹 Data quality\n\nDedupe/diff steps make re-runs safe: the same input twice will not create duplicate records. If you change the key fields, clear n8n's dedupe memory (node → 'Clear stored keys') before the next run.","width":360,"height":260,"color":1},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[610,-290],"id":"663f7019-9987-29fb-36fb-c7b2fcff6587","name":"🧹 Data quality"},{"parameters":{"content":"## 🛠 Customize me\n\nQuick wins: point the data nodes at your own accounts (see 🔑 lines on each card), adjust the trigger cadence, and tune thresholds/labels to your order ops process. Every node card explains its role — safe to extend at any marked branch.","width":360,"height":260,"color":4},"type":"n8n-nodes-base.stickyNote","typeVersion":1,"position":[1030,-290],"id":"ae6063a8-80f4-8029-f879-87546e536ec1","name":"🛠 Customize me"}],"connections":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute HMAC Signature","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute HMAC Signature":{"main":[[{"node":"Signature Valid?","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Signature Valid?":{"main":[[{"node":"Map to Canonical Schema","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Reject (HTTP 401)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Map to Canonical Schema":{"main":[[{"node":"Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Acknowledge Fast (HTTP 202)":{"main":[[{"node":"Route by Event Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Route by Event Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Handle 'opened' → Notion","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Handle 'closed' → Forward API","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Handle 'reopened' → Forward API","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Log Unrecognized Kind","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'opened' → Notion":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'closed' → Forward API":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":1}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Handle 'reopened' → Forward API":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":2}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Log Unrecognized Kind":{"main":[[{"node":"Consolidate Handling","type":"main","index":3}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Consolidate Handling":{"main":[[{"node":"Fingerprint for Idempotency","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fingerprint for Idempotency":{"main":[[{"node":"Drop Already-Processed Items","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Drop Already-Processed Items":{"main":[[{"node":"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Offload to Post-Process Sub-workflow":{"main":[[{"node":"Record Sub-workflow Result","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Record Sub-workflow Result":{"main":[[{"node":"Serialize Run Output (CSV)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Serialize Run Output (CSV)":{"main":[[{"node":"Archive Row Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Archive Row Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Stamp Completion Time","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Stamp Completion Time":{"main":[[{"node":"Persist Run Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Persist Run Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Enrich with Reference Data","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Enrich with Reference Data":{"main":[[{"node":"Fold In Enrichment Fields","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Fold In Enrichment Fields":{"main":[[{"node":"Load Previous Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Load Previous Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Compute Drift vs Snapshot","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Compute Drift vs Snapshot":{"main":[[{"node":"Guard Non-Empty email","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Guard Non-Empty email":{"main":[[{"node":"Save Execution Metadata","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Save Execution Metadata":{"main":[[{"node":"Sort Orders Newest First","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Sort Orders Newest First":{"main":[[{"node":"Summarize Run Stats","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Summarize Run Stats":{"main":[[{"node":"Append Audit Row (Notion)","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Append Audit Row (Notion)":{"main":[[{"node":"Send Summary to Microsoft Teams","type":"main","index":0}],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Capture Failure Context":{"main":[[{"node":"Escalate Failure to Slack","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Escalate Failure to Slack":{"main":[[{"node":"Park in Dead-Letter Queue","type":"main","index":0}]]},"Send Summary to Microsoft Teams":{"main":[[],[{"node":"Capture Failure Context","type":"main","index":0}]]}},"active":false,"settings":{"executionOrder":"v1","saveDataErrorExecution":"all","saveManualExecutions":true,"executionTimeout":3600},"meta":{"templateCredsSetupCompleted":false},"tags":[],"pinData":{"Receive Inbound Webhook":[{"json":{"orderId":"ORD-55211","email":"chris.owusu@example.com","total":129.99,"status":"paid"}},{"json":{"orderId":"ORD-55212","email":"nina.silva@example.com","total":64.5,"status":"pending"}}]},"versionId":"ceba99b5-8ccc-4d99-87c6-e863fdd7b590","id":"FDX09235"}